00:00:03:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:03:030000.Dialogue: Hi. Did Sheldon change the Wi-Fi password again?

00:00:06:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:06:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, it's Penny already eats our food. She can pay for Wi-Fi.

00:00:13:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:13:150000.Dialogue: Okay. If you can't get me to stop eating your food, what makes you think you can get me to stop using your Wi-Fi?

00:00:18:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:18:190000.Dialogue: I believe that you're capable of great change. Like when I finally got you to stop saying Valentimes Day

00:00:26:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:26:150000.Dialogue: You want to hear something weird?

00:00:28:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:28:140000.Dialogue: In the year 2000, Pope John Paul II was named an honorary Harlem Globetrotter.

00:00:39:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:39:200000.Dialogue: You asked Penny if she wanted to hear something weird.

00:00:42:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:42:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, because I have something weird to tell her.

00:00:45:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:45:140000.Dialogue: Oh. I thought it was a game.

00:00:51:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:51:200000.Dialogue: There's this guy, Jimmy Speckerman, who used to torment me in high school. He sent me a message through Facebook. He's in town and wants to have drinks.

00:01:00:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:00:130000.Dialogue: Okay, Penny, if it were a game, here are your choices. An e-mail from an old acquaintance, or the head of one of the largest religious institutions in the world slam dunking to Sweet Georgia Brown. Pick.

00:01:14:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:14:210000.Dialogue: Just do it, 'cause he's not gonna let it go.

00:01:22:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:22:230000.Dialogue: What are you gonna do about your bully? Are you gonna see him?

00:01:26:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:26:180000.Dialogue: Is this the fellow who peed in your Hawaiian Punch?

00:01:30:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:30:030000.Dialogue: No, that was a different guy.

00:01:32:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:32:130000.Dialogue: Was he the one who wedgied you so hard, your testicle reascended, and you spent your whole Christmas break waiting for it to come back down?

00:01:42:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:42:140000.Dialogue: No, that was a different, different guy.

00:01:45:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:45:200000.Dialogue: Was he the one who used your head to open a nut?

00:01:51:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:51:220000.Dialogue: Oh, oh, oh. Was he the one who made you eat your arm hair?

00:01:57:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:57:200000.Dialogue: No, but, actually, that was this guy's sister.

00:02:00:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:00:220000.Dialogue: All right, well, what do you think he wants?

00:02:04:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:04:030000.Dialogue: You know, the holidays are just around the corner. Maybe he wants to see if he can lodge the other testicle up there.

00:02:09:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:09:050000.Dialogue: I told you. That was a different guy.

00:02:12:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:12:070000.Dialogue: Hmm. That's too bad. We could have spent New Year's Eve waiting for the ball to drop.

00:02:50:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:50:010000.Dialogue: It's 2:00 a.m. What are you doing up?

00:02:52:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:52:050000.Dialogue: Nobel Prize acceptance ceremony streaming live from Stockholm.

00:02:57:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:57:050000.Dialogue: Sure. You want to see what all the scientists are wearing this year.

00:03:01:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:01:140000.Dialogue: Look at these men. They've managed to win the top science prize in the world with no more understanding of the quantum underpinnings of the expansion of the early universe than God gave a goose.

00:03:15:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:15:110000.Dialogue: You should pay attention, Leonard. Someday this could be you up there.

00:03:20:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:20:200000.Dialogue: So, what's got you up? Did you have a bad clam?

00:03:27:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:27:180000.Dialogue: I don't watch you 24 hours a day. I don't know what you do.

00:03:31:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:31:190000.Dialogue: It's this Jimmy Speckerman thing. I can't decide if I should agree to see him or not. Of course that might be because the last time I ran into him, he made me floss with my own shoelaces.

00:03:46:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:46:040000.Dialogue: Look at Dr. Saul Perlmutter up there, clutching that Nobel Prize. What's the matter, Saul? You afraid someone's going to steal it? Like you stole Einstein's cosmological constant?

00:03:57:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:57:080000.Dialogue: You know what? I am tired of living in fear of this guy. I'm gonna go see him and finally say all the things I should have said in high school. You know, Pick on someone your own size You did not have sex with my mother.

00:04:12:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:12:210000.Dialogue: And Yes, I do know why I'm hitting myself.

00:04:16:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:16:210000.Dialogue: Oh, now Perlmutter's shaking the king's hand. Yeah, check for your watch, Gustaf. He might have lifted it.

00:04:24:210000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:04:24:210000.Dialogue: I love this dress. How come I never see you wear it?

00:04:28:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:28:220000.Dialogue: 'Cause when I wear it, it's a shirt.

00:04:34:230000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:04:34:230000.Dialogue: Oh, they all went with Leonard to confront his childhood bully.

00:04:38:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:38:020000.Dialogue: Oh, terrific. High school quarterback against four mathletes.

00:04:43:070000.Speaker: Amy
00:04:43:070000.Dialogue: When Leonard gets back, I'd love to check his serotonin levels. Do you think he'd let me draw a syringe full of his blood?

00:04:48:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:48:190000.Dialogue: Hmm, he's not crazy about needles, but if you get him to go jogging, it'll just pour out of his nose.

00:04:55:090000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:04:55:090000.Dialogue: I don't think I can meet the girl who was always mean to me. Tammy Bodnick. One time while I was in gym class, she stole all my clothes and left an elf costume in my locker.

00:05:08:110000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:05:08:110000.Dialogue: Worst part was, it was too big.

00:05:12:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:12:230000.Dialogue: That's nothing. In ninth grade, the girls put Rogaine in my hand lotion.

00:05:18:120000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:18:120000.Dialogue: Within six months, the nicknames began to fly. I think the one that hurt the most was Gorilla Fingers Fowler.

00:05:28:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:28:140000.Dialogue: Oh. I don't know. I guess my school was a nice place. We didn't really have bullies.

00:05:33:210000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:33:210000.Dialogue: Come on, no one ever gave anyone mean nicknames or picked on them or put gum in their hairy knuckles so the school nurse had to use peanut butter to get it out?

00:05:43:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:43:000000.Dialogue: No, we weren't really like that. I mean, look, we played pranks on each other, but it was never mean. Like, okay, this one girl, Kathy Geiger, got really good grades, so we blindfolded her, tied her up and left her in a cornfield overnight.

00:05:57:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:57:090000.Dialogue: No, it was funny. Everyone laughed.

00:06:02:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:02:060000.Dialogue: Uh, probably. It's hard to say. She kind of had an ear of corn in her mouth.

00:06:06:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:06:220000.Dialogue: Who would have thought Fuzzy Fingers Fowler is best friends with a bully?

00:06:13:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:13:030000.Dialogue: What? I was not a bully.

00:06:15:190000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:15:190000.Dialogue: Kind of sounds like you were. And maybe a felon.

00:06:22:120000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:22:120000.Dialogue: Shh. That's how you wind up in a cornfield.

00:06:33:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:33:040000.Dialogue: How about that guy? He looks like he'd hate you.

00:06:37:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:37:110000.Dialogue: You know, I can really do this by myself.

00:06:39:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:39:200000.Dialogue: Hey, we're here to support you, buddy.

00:06:41:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:41:110000.Dialogue: No, you're not. You're here to see if I get my underwear pulled over my head.

00:06:49:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:49:070000.Dialogue: So, have you figured out what you're going to say to him?

00:06:51:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:51:100000.Dialogue: You bet. I am going to make him apologize for all the crap he pulled on me in school.

00:06:56:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:56:210000.Dialogue: That's quite a list. I can't read your handwriting. What's that word?

00:07:15:110000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:07:15:110000.Dialogue: Holy crap, man, it's good to see you.

00:07:17:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:17:210000.Dialogue: Yeah. You, too. Uh, Jimmy, this is Sheldon and Raj and Howard.

00:07:21:210000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:07:21:210000.Dialogue: Hi. Fellas... Hey, can I get a beer? Wow. Look at you. Little Leonard Hofstadter. I hear you're a big-time scientist now.

00:07:29:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:29:170000.Dialogue: And there's the first zinger. Ouch.

00:07:34:200000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:07:34:200000.Dialogue: Okay? Come on, I read online you're a physicist at a university, you won some medal.

00:07:42:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:42:220000.Dialogue: Congratulations? The Newcomb medal? Oh, please. That's the scientific equivalent of a smiley face sticker on your homework.

00:07:50:030000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:07:50:030000.Dialogue: From what I read, it sounded like a big deal.

00:07:52:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:52:150000.Dialogue: Oh, good Lord, are we going to stand here and listen to him tear Leonard apart like this?

00:07:58:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:58:060000.Dialogue: Hey, I won a Newcomb medal, too.

00:08:02:190000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:02:190000.Dialogue: You should have seen this guy back in the day. Huh? He was so little, he could fit in just about anywhere. Lockers, trash cans. Oh, man, how did you get inside that backpack?

00:08:14:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:14:040000.Dialogue: Oh, I can't take all the credit. You helped a lot.

00:08:18:060000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:18:060000.Dialogue: We were practically a comedy team.

00:08:20:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:20:040000.Dialogue: Like the Black Death and Europe.

00:08:23:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:23:200000.Dialogue: Jimmy, I'm kind of curious why you wanted to see me.

00:08:27:170000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:27:170000.Dialogue: Okay, here it is. I have this great money-making idea. I just need a gear head to get it to the finish line.

00:08:33:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:33:040000.Dialogue: Technically, Howard's the gear head. Leonard's just a dime store laser jockey.

00:08:39:090000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:39:090000.Dialogue: This is just between us, right?

00:08:41:020000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:41:020000.Dialogue: Okay. What do you think about a pair of glasses that makes any movie you want into 3D?

00:08:46:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:46:180000.Dialogue: That sounds amazing. First movie I'm watching-- Annie.

00:08:53:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:53:060000.Dialogue: How exactly would these glasses work?

00:08:56:040000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:08:56:040000.Dialogue: How the hell should I know? That's why I need a nerd.

00:08:59:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:59:050000.Dialogue: I don't think something like that's even possible.

00:09:03:010000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:09:03:010000.Dialogue: Aw, come on, you can figure it out. You're like the smartest guy I've ever known.

00:09:06:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:06:090000.Dialogue: The smartest...?! All right, you know, I may not have a firm grasp on sarcasm, but even I know that was a doozy.

00:09:15:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:15:200000.Dialogue: Leonard, you can't live in fear of this man forever.

00:09:19:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:19:230000.Dialogue: You clearly don't. What my spineless friend lacks the courage to say is you're a terrible person who took advantage of his tiny size, his uncoordinated nature and his congenital lack of masculinity.

00:09:33:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:33:140000.Dialogue: Leonard, I platonically love you, man, but face it, you're a mess.

00:09:41:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:41:120000.Dialogue: I think what he's trying to say is that maybe in high school you picked on me a little bit. A little bit?

00:09:48:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:48:210000.Dialogue: The man Super Glued Hershey's Kisses to your nipples.

00:09:54:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:54:060000.Dialogue: That's funny because those aren't the kind of kisses you want on your nipples.

00:10:00:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:00:150000.Dialogue: This is a list of your heinous acts against Leonard. One of which is certainly the cause of him wetting his bed well into his teens.

00:10:16:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:16:120000.Dialogue: Nancy. You called me Nancy for three years.

00:10:24:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:24:020000.Dialogue: You really need to work on your penmanship.

00:10:27:090000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:10:27:090000.Dialogue: Oh, man, I... I don't know what to say. I always thought we were just having some fun.

00:10:37:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:37:210000.Dialogue: You're being too kind, Leonard. You ruined him.

00:10:45:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:45:230000.Dialogue: I help the weak. It's yet another way I'm exactly like Batman.

00:10:49:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:49:180000.Dialogue: Hey, for the record, Jimmy wasn't the reason I wet the bed. That one has my mother written all over it.

00:11:02:040000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:02:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:02:040000.Dialogue: Anyway, I'm really sorry I made fun of your stutter in high school.

00:11:05:190000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:05:190000.Speaker: Bernadette

00:11:07:210000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:07:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:07:210000.Dialogue: Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Oh, God, just finish the sentence.

00:11:18:050000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:18:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:18:050000.Dialogue: Okay, well, I'm sorry you feel that way. Bye. No one wants to hear my apologies.

00:11:24:110000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:24:110000.Speaker: Amy
00:11:24:110000.Dialogue: I think your mistake is doing it over the phone. If they could look into your eyes, they'd melt.

00:11:31:040000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:31:040000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:31:040000.Dialogue: Penny, it doesn't matter what you did in the past. You're a good person now.

00:11:34:230000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:34:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:34:230000.Dialogue: That's easy for you to say. You weren't just called a b-b-b-b-bitch.

00:11:39:140000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:39:140000.Speaker: Amy
00:11:39:140000.Dialogue: Perhaps you could assuage your guilt through altruism.

00:11:46:210000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:46:210000.Speaker: Amy
00:11:46:210000.Dialogue: Which word's tripping you up? Assuage, or altruism?

00:11:52:060000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:52:060000.Speaker: Penny

00:11:56:050000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:56:050000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:56:050000.Dialogue: You'll feel better by doing something nice for someone.

00:11:58:230000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:11:58:230000.Speaker: Penny

00:12:02:220000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:02:220000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:02:220000.Dialogue: Every other week I serve at a soup kitchen downtown.

00:12:05:190000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:05:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:05:190000.Dialogue: Ooh, I can't do that. If I stand over a steaming pot, my hair just goes boing!

00:12:12:070000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:12:070000.Speaker: Penny

00:12:13:190000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:13:190000.Speaker: Amy
00:12:13:190000.Dialogue: There's Habitat for Humanity-- building houses for the poor.

00:12:16:160000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:16:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:16:160000.Dialogue: Okay, come on, I don't even have my own house-- I'm going to build one for someone else?

00:12:20:020000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:20:020000.Speaker: Amy
00:12:20:020000.Dialogue: How about donating some of your clothes?

00:12:23:130000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:23:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:23:130000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, that's perfect. 'Cause I have so many clothes I don't wear, and they're just taking up space, and I go shopping to buy more stuff and I have no place to put it. This will totally fix that.

00:12:33:060000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:33:060000.Speaker: Bernadette

00:12:34:200000.Scene: Penny’s bedroom. Penny is on the phone.
00:12:34:200000.Speaker: Penny

00:12:41:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:41:030000.Dialogue: Oh, half and half instead of whole milk?

00:12:46:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:46:030000.Dialogue: Seven little marshmallows, no more no less?

00:12:48:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:48:010000.Dialogue: You got one for good luck. I'll get it.

00:12:52:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:52:200000.Dialogue: One for good luck. Must be the kind of math they do at Princeton.

00:13:04:180000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:13:04:180000.Dialogue: I want to apologize for... stapling your balls and...

00:13:10:020000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:13:10:020000.Dialogue: ...throwing you naked in the girls' locker room, stuffing that parrot down your pants.

00:13:31:170000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:13:31:170000.Dialogue: Yeah. I just hope you can forgive me.

00:13:47:200000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:13:47:200000.Dialogue: Yeah, yeah, yeah. I drive better drunk. You know, it makes you pay attention.

00:13:54:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:54:170000.Dialogue: No, no, no, come on in. I'll make you a cup of coffee.

00:14:01:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:01:000000.Dialogue: Sheldon, we can't let him drive.

00:14:04:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:04:070000.Dialogue: Then take away his keys and make him wander the streets with the other drunks.

00:14:10:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:10:110000.Dialogue: You remember Sheldon and Raj and Howard.

00:14:16:020000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:14:16:020000.Dialogue: It's funny, huh, Leonard? Back in school, I was the winner and you were the loser. And now we're reversed. You're the winner.

00:14:24:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:24:000000.Dialogue: You'd think a winner could make a decent cup of cocoa.

00:14:28:160000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:14:28:160000.Dialogue: You mind if I use your bathroom?

00:14:34:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:34:160000.Dialogue: How about that? After all these years, your big bad high school bully finally apologizes.

00:14:41:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:41:030000.Dialogue: Yeah. It kind of rekindles your faith in the basic goodness of people.

00:14:46:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:46:020000.Dialogue: You know what would be nice?

00:14:49:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:49:100000.Dialogue: As a symbolic gesture to all the bullies who've tormented us for years, we open our home to Jimmy and once he's asleep we kill him.

00:15:04:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:04:100000.Dialogue: I said it would be nice-- I didn't say we should do it.

00:15:09:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:09:220000.Dialogue: I feel just like Mother Teresa. Except for the virgin part. That ship sailed a long time ago.

00:15:18:050000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:15:18:050000.Dialogue: I think Mother Teresa would have washed the clothes first.

00:15:22:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:22:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, I bet her laundry room wasn't down five flights of stairs.

00:15:26:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:26:200000.Dialogue: You know, giving really is better than receiving. I used to think it was such a cliche, but it seems to be the... Look at these cute jeans someone just threw away.

00:15:42:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:42:200000.Dialogue: Yes, to a poor waitress who loves a boot cut.

00:15:48:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:48:140000.Dialogue: Come on, they would be so cute on me... They go great with this sweater!

00:15:52:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:15:52:220000.Dialogue: I don't think Mother Teresa... Oh, that is adorable.

00:16:17:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:17:070000.Dialogue: What was I supposed to do? He needed a place to sleep it off.

00:16:20:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:20:120000.Dialogue: You're soft. This world's going to chew you up and spit you out.

00:16:40:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:40:040000.Dialogue: Yeah, you did. So, uh, listen, it was great to see you again. And thanks for the apology.

00:16:49:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:49:040000.Dialogue: For all the crappy stuff you did to me in high school.

00:16:52:080000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:16:52:080000.Dialogue: Geez, you're still harping on that? What a puss.

00:16:58:100000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:16:58:100000.Dialogue: It's good. You really know your way around a kitchen, Nancy.

00:17:04:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:04:110000.Dialogue: I'm not going to say I told you so, but we could have killed him.

00:17:11:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:11:040000.Dialogue: I might kill him right now.

00:17:14:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:14:050000.Dialogue: The Dark Knight has your back. He's scared, but he has your back.

00:17:19:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:19:080000.Dialogue: Okay, Jimmy, it's time for you to go.

00:17:21:130000.Speaker: Jimmy
00:17:21:130000.Dialogue: Yeah, all right, let me just finish this.

00:17:23:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:23:010000.Dialogue: No, you're done. I want you out of my apartment right now.

00:17:31:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:31:210000.Dialogue: Don't answer that. It's a trick question. I speak from experience.

00:17:37:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:37:170000.Dialogue: I'm not afraid of you anymore, Jimmy. Now get out! Uh-oh.

00:17:46:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:46:170000.Dialogue: You did it, Leonard, you stood up to your bully.

00:17:48:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:48:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, I feel pretty good about myself.

00:17:53:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:53:030000.Dialogue: You think we can outrun him?

00:17:55:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:55:120000.Dialogue: I don't need to outrun him, I just need to outrun you.

00:18:04:150000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:18:04:150000.Dialogue: I don't feel good about this.

00:18:06:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:06:060000.Dialogue: Then sit in the car and keep it running.

00:18:09:060000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:09:060000.Dialogue: You were right-- a whole new load.

00:18:14:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:14:220000.Dialogue: Come on, yoga top. Mama needs a new yoga top.

00:18:17:210000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:17:210000.Dialogue: Check it out, Bernadette, suede boots, your size.

00:18:20:130000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:18:20:130000.Dialogue: God, they're cute. Oh, why did they have to be cute?

00:18:25:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:25:080000.Dialogue: Wait, wait, wait, guys, just hang on.

00:18:32:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:32:090000.Dialogue: Look at us. What are we doing?

00:18:35:210000.Speaker: Amy
00:18:35:210000.Dialogue: I was gleefully following you to a life of crime, looking forward to the day we might be cell mates.

00:18:47:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:47:210000.Dialogue: You know, this is wrong. Let's put everything back. Here.

00:19:04:080000.Speaker: Bernadette (taking boots and running)
00:19:04:080000.Dialogue: It's okay, I serve soup to poor people!
